                <h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>How many times have you gone to a website that looked a little suspicious? Or clicked a download link in an email that was sent from an email address you didn't recognise? Or maybe even picked up a USB flash drive that you found on the floor and plugged into your computer?</p>
<p>If you've done any of these things, hopefully you had antivirus installed on your device that was able to protect you from anything malicious! Antivirus acts as a shield between your computer and the outside world to try and prevent your computer being infected with viruses by hackers!</p>
<p>If you don't have antivirus installed though, it's important that you download it as soon as possible! A great, free piece of antivirus software is <a href="https://www.avast.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Avast Antivirus</a>. It's available for Windows, Android, MacOS and iOS. So you can keep all of your devices secure... for FREE! There is no excuse for not having it installed.</p>
<div class="blog-affiliate-one"></div>
<h2>Do I Really Need Antivirus?</h2>
<p><strong>YES!</strong></p>
<p>I often get asked by people if they really need to get antivirus if they make sure they are safe online. But the problem is that you can never fully guarantee that you are safe online. Each and every day, hackers and virus creators are looking for new ways that they can use to infect your computer. So, it can be difficult to stay up to date with the latest security practices. To make your life easier, install antivirus to improve your chances of staying safe online!</p>
<p>According to <a href="https://www.av-test.org/en/statistics/malware/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AV-Test</a>, the AV-Test Institute discover over 350,000 new pieces of malware everyday! On 31 August 2019, they reported that there is around 937.61m pieces of malware. That's a lot of malware!</p>
<h2>Download Avast Antivirus For Free</h2>
<p>There are plenty of different pieces of antivirus software that you can download online and use. However, I personally recommend using Avast Antivirus as I have used it for many years across many different devices. In fact, it is one of the first things that I download when I get a new Android phone, desktop PC or laptop!</p>
<p>Use the link below to download it for free now to start securing your device now from viruses and malware!</p>
<p class="text-center">
  	<a href="https://www.avast.com" class="btn fill-style" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
	  Download Avast Antivirus&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-external-link-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  </a>
</p>

